</div><div class="info-panel__citations info-panel__item"><a href="#tab-citations" class="btn btn--inverse btn--slim" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="View Citations" aria-label="View Citations"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-format_quote"></i></a></div><div class="info-panel__formats info-panel__item"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Go to purchase options" aria-label="Go to purchase options"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="link-text">Get Access</span></a></div></div></div></div></header><div data-core-nav="header" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-nav-wrapper core-container" aria-label="Article navigation"><div><button aria-controls="article_sections_menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle section navigation menu"><i class="icon-list" aria-hidden="true"></i><span>Contents</span></button><nav id="article_sections_menu" aria-label="Contents" data-core-nav="article"><ul><li><a href="#abstract">Abstract</a></li><li><a href="#core-sec-figures">Figures</a></li><li><a href="#bibliography">References</a></li></ul></nav></div><nav id="article_collateral_menu"><ul class="collateral-pill" data-core-nav="collateral"><li><a href="#core-collateral-info" aria-controls="core-collateral-info" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Information & Authors" title="Information & Authors" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-info"></i><span class="sr-only">Information & Authors</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-metrics" aria-controls="core-collateral-metrics" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Metrics & Citations" title="Metrics & Citations" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-metrics"></i><span class="sr-only">Metrics & Citations</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-controls="core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Get Access" title="Get Access" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="sr-only">Get Access</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-references" aria-controls="core-collateral-references" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="References" title="References" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-references"></i><span class="sr-only">References</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-figures" aria-controls="core-collateral-figures" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Figures" title="Figures" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-photo"></i><span class="sr-only">Figures</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-tables" aria-controls="core-collateral-tables" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Tables" title="Tables" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-table"></i><span class="sr-only">Tables</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-media" aria-controls="core-collateral-media" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Media" title="Media" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-play-circle-filled"></i><span class="sr-only">Media</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-share" aria-controls="core-collateral-share" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Share" title="Share" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-share"></i><span class="sr-only">Share</span></a></li></ul></nav></div></div><div data-core-wrapper="content"><div id="abstracts" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="abstract" property="abstract" typeof="Text" role="doc-abstract"><h2 property="name">Abstract</h2><div role="paragraph">Blunt polytrauma remains a leading cause of death and disability worldwide. With the major advances in computed tomography (CT) technology over the past decade, whole-body CT is increasingly recognized as the emerging standard for providing rapid and accurate diagnoses within the narrow therapeutic window afforded to trauma victims with multiple severe injuries. With a single continuous acquisition, whole-body CT angiography is able to demonstrate all potentially injured organs, as well as vascular and bone structures, from the circle of Willis to the symphysis pubis. As its use becomes more widespread, the large volume of information inherent to whole-body CT poses new challenges to radiologists in providing efficient and timely interpretation. An awareness of trauma scoring systems and injury mechanisms is essential to maintain an appropriate level of suspicion in the search for multiple injuries, and the use of multiplanar reformation and three-dimensional postprocessing techniques is important to maximize efficiency in the search. Knowledge of the key injuries that require urgent surgical or percutaneous intervention, including major vascular injuries and active hemorrhage, diaphragmatic rupture, unstable spinal fractures, pancreatic injuries with ductal involvement, and injuries to the mesentery and hollow viscera, is also necessary.</div><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2012</div></section></div></div><section id="bodymatter" data-extent="bodymatter" property="articleBody" typeof="Text"><div class="core-container"><section aria-labelledby="denial-block-title" class="denial-block "><h2 id="denial-block-title" class="denial-block__title">Get full access to this article</h2><p class="denial-block__text">View all available purchase options and get full access to this article.</p><div class="denial-block__cta"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span>Get Access</span></a></div><footer class="denial-block__footer"><span>Already a Subscriber? </span><span>Sign in as an </span><a href="/action/showLogin?redirectUri=/doi/10.1148/rg.323115099">individual</a><span> or via your </span><a href="/action/ssostart?uri=/doi/10.1148/rg.323115099">institution</a></footer></section></div></section><section id="backmatter" data-extent="backmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="core-sec-figures" data-type="figures"><h2>Figures</h2><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig01a.jpeg" height="1280" width="733" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig01a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig01b.jpeg" height="1035" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig01b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig02a.jpeg" height="1280" width="871" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig02a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig02b.jpeg" height="1280" width="899" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig02b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig02c.jpeg" height="1046" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig02c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig02d.jpeg" height="1022" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig02d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig03a.jpeg" height="1181" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig03a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig03b.jpeg" height="1280" width="1199" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig03b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig04a.jpeg" height="1280" width="824" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig04a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig04b.jpeg" height="1007" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig04b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig04c.jpeg" height="958" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig04c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig05.jpeg" height="1280" width="942" aria-labelledby="fig05" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5</span> Burst injury in a 59-year-old patient who was involved in a high-speed motor vehicle collision. Sagittal oblique collimated whole-body CT angiographic image obtained at the level of the aorta shows a large diaphragmatic rupture (arrow), with herniated bowel and mesentery extending into the right hemithorax, a result of a burst-type force and laceration from rib and sternal fractures. An aortic intimal injury with focal dissection is seen (arrowhead). The patient underwent diaphragmatic and pericardial repair, internal mammary artery ligation, splenectomy, surgical drainage of the left kidney, and left segmental colon resection to treat other injuries. An aortic endovascular stent graft was subsequently placed. Intimal injury of the high cervical right carotid artery was treated conservatively.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig05">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig06a.jpeg" height="1280" width="677" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig06a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig06b.jpeg" height="1043" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig06b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig06c.jpeg" height="1092" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig06c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig07a.jpeg" height="1280" width="430" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig07a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig07b.jpeg" height="1280" width="473" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig07b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig08a.jpeg" height="1280" width="892" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig08a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig08b.jpeg" height="1083" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig08b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig08c.jpeg" height="1071" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig08c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig09a.jpeg" height="1280" width="531" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig09a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig09b.jpeg" height="1280" width="551" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig09b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig10a.jpeg" height="1280" width="488" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig10b.jpeg" height="1280" width="466" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig11a.jpeg" height="1280" width="490" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig11b.jpeg" height="1280" width="589" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig11c.jpeg" height="1238" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig11c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig12.jpeg" height="1215" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig12" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12</span> Blunt cerebrovascular injuries in the same patient as in <a href="#fig05">Figure 5</a>. Integrated neck CT angiographic image shows multiple segments of luminal irregularity in the right midcervical internal carotid artery (oval), a finding consistent with a Biffl grade I blunt cerebrovascular injury. Systemic anticoagulation therapy was contraindicated in this case because of the presence of additional injuries; however, follow-up angiography performed 4 days later showed mild (&lt;25%) stenosis with no compromise in flow to the right hemisphere.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig12">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig13a.jpeg" height="1280" width="873" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig13b.jpeg" height="987" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig14.jpeg" height="1280" width="1202" aria-labelledby="fig14" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14</span> Pancreatic duct disruption in a 36-year-old patient involved in a motor vehicle collision. Coronal collimated MIP whole-body CT angiographic image obtained at the level of the pancreas shows transection of the pancreatic neck (arrow). Secondary signs of pancreatic injury, including adjacent free fluid and fat stranding (arrowheads), also are seen. Complete pancreatic duct disruption was confirmed at surgery, and distal pancreatectomy was performed.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig14">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig15a.jpeg" height="1280" width="682" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig15a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig15b.jpeg" height="1204" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig15b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig15c.jpeg" height="1228" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig15c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig16a.jpeg" height="1011" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig16a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig16b.jpeg" height="1007" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig16b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.323115099/asset/images/115099fig17a.jpeg" height="1280" width="607" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.323115099&amp;id=fig17a">Download as PowerPoint